Because I felt depraved of it from almost everyone in my life, I was desperate for almost everything. You could say I'm Dante and Vergil from Devil May Cry. I wanted to be accepted and understood, but I was too silent because I was an introvert.

I never understood why I felt like an outcast in my family, until I realized I was an introvert. I didn't know how to grow up as an adult. All I knew was that I was an alternative nerd who had the heart of a child. And now here I am, very mature yet still afraid to fail.

I had dreams and goals, but I didn't know how to execute them without putting too much expectations on myself. Because I was afraid to fail as an author. Because I wanted to be without failure in my life. Because I wanted something out of life that wasn't cheap.

I wouldn't have focused on the what if scenario of being a successful author and I would have just taken my time doing something. But because I was lost and confused, because I haven't been able to figure out my life, I was in limbo for the next twenty eight years.

If you truly wanna know why weeabos, Otakus and emos you may hate exist, it's because they're burnt out on life. Many of them experience life in the harshest way and are unable to figure their lives out in a healthy manner, so they turn to extremes because they're in pain.

Life goes on, but you alone choose how to live your life. So don't worry about the naysayers who disapprove with you. Screw the Nazis and all white supremacist groups. The future belongs to diversity, not ignorance.

To hell with those who hate on you for being different and not being good enough in their eyes just because you come from a different race, gender and sexuality. If you have to cut certain people off, go for it. Toxicity doesn't have to be in your life.

Still, don't be an asshole to those who try to do good things for others, even if you think what they do is boring and unrelatable. You can be independent and strong, no one is the same even when they're independent.

No human should dictate anyone's life no matter how boring or unrelatable they think their lives are. No one is the same. Everyone is different. We are all capable of being both non-conforming and conforming at the same time or at different times.

Yes, be boring. Be unrelatable. But remember to be a good person or just a person who does good things for yourselves and others. You don't even have to change who you are for anyone. I don't have expectations for anyone who's different than me.

In fact, your life will be filled a lot of boring shit others will find unacceptable. Even at your highest point in real life, some people might still find you boring. And sadly, unrelatable. But don't fret. Because you are loved.

That being said, live your lives to your fullest and do good things instead of bad. You'll find that those who do good things are the ones who care about others. I know that doing good may sound too boring, but you know what? You will often do boring things.

Through experience, we learn about ourselves and the world in every generation. That being said, learning from the past is also important. So the idea of ignoring it is impossible. Remember those who came before you. Don't forget to teach your kids this too.

And whatever type of love it is, let it known that you're cared for and not alone. Yes, the world is hell and you will go through it before you enter heaven. But in the end, even if you died alone, someone out there would be your rock forever.

To be truthful, if you're willing to be more than just your pain in your life, then you are a lot stronger than you realize. Yes, you could be broken, but that doesn't mean you have to accept defeat. Why? Because someone out there loves and support you.

And if it is, love to your hearts' content. Eventually you will make mistakes. Just remember that, even if you were a machine, you will make mistakes. Unfortunately, life will sometimes be complicated and you won't know how to handle what comes your way.

In any case, you just need certain things in your life, like experience, knowledge, hope, fairness and most importantly, love. Love for yourself and love for others. It can be any type of love: familial, platonic or romantic. It doesn't have to be all of the above.

Everything will come in place slowly. There's no need to rush into anything if you're not ready yet. Just take a deep breath and try not to worry. In reality, you may not get everything you want in life. And that's okay. You don't need everything.

You live only once, but that doesn't mean you have to be an asshole to people who don't need your trolling around them. If you haven't figured out your life yet, there's no need to accept defeat and let your life pass you by. Just take your time and relax.
